{"TopicId":220267,"ForumId":208,"TopicTitle":"Icons scaling incorrectly in map view","CreatedByName":"Guitarman_0511","CreatedById":231016,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-26T11:23:14Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Guitarman_0511","CreatedById":231016,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-26T11:23:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.1.5 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 11 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Ryzen 9 3900x | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0RX5700XT | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E32GB 3600MHz CL16\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI noticed that after the patch some Icons are not scaling correctly anymore, as can be seen in the screenshot.\u003Cbr\u003E\nI did not do anything special, I just opened the map and the saw the Icon like this\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ipslightbox=\u0022\u0022 alt=\u002220231025202425_1.jpg.9758057dfa7d4716802\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/uploads/monthly_2023_10/20231025202425_1.jpg.9758057dfa7d47168020cf65d9f944fc.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cstyle type=\u0022text/css\u0022\u003E\r\n.ipsImage {\r\nwidth: 900px !important;\r\n}\u003C/style\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vortygont","CreatedById":223549,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-26T21:27:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI also noticed rescaled incorrectly icons and wanted to do report about this, but here it is\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-26T21:31:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI hate this bug so much - it\u0027s been annoying me since the game launched one way or another. Those pixelated icons look \u003Cstrong\u003Eterrible\u003C/strong\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dansiegel30","CreatedById":225462,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-26T21:50:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224333866\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022220267\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221698355896\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022219348\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vl3d\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 minutes ago, Vl3d said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI hate this bug so much - it\u0027s been annoying me since the game launched one way or another. Those pixelated icons look \u003Cstrong\u003Eterrible\u003C/strong\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAgreed, if the dev team loves retro, they can wear bell bottoms with penny loafers in the office...but dot matrix died in the 90s, and it should stay dead.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RaBDawG","CreatedById":206005,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-21T12:40:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.2.0 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Winsows 10 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0AMD Ryzen 9 5900X 12-Core Processor 3.70 GHz | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0AMD Ryzen 9 5900X 12-Core Processor 3.70 GHz | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E32GB\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs this a Bug or by design?\u00A0 I can\u0027t even click on Minmus to target it because my probe that is in orbit\u0027s icon is 5x the size of minmus on map.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cstyle type=\u0022text/css\u0022\u003E\r\n.ipsImage {\r\nwidth: 900px !important;\r\n}\u003C/style\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Space Peacock","CreatedById":224498,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-21T16:20:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/231016-guitarman_0511/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022231016\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/231016-guitarman_0511/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Guitarman_0511\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0moved this report out of the archive\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/206005-rabdawg/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022206005\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/206005-rabdawg/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@RaBDawG\u003C/a\u003E merged your report\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dandoesstuff","CreatedById":223454,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-21T19:43:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.2.0 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 10 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0AMD Ryzen 3 3200G | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0GTX 1050 Ti | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E16GB 3200MHz\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, I was trying to select minmus to go to it but instead the icon of a vessel turned huge infront of it, so i couldn\u0027t target minmus\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ipslightbox=\u0022\u0022 alt=\u0022canttarget.png.8be0d73f09f7031dbb30da139\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/uploads/monthly_2023_12/canttarget.png.8be0d73f09f7031dbb30da1393fe27d6.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cstyle type=\u0022text/css\u0022\u003E\r\n.ipsImage {\r\nwidth: 900px !important;\r\n}\u003C/style\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Space Peacock","CreatedById":224498,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-22T13:20:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/223454-dandoesstuff/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022223454\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/223454-dandoesstuff/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@dandoesstuff\u003C/a\u003E merged your report\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"krbvax","CreatedById":231742,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-31T04:29:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEasy reproducer: launch a ship to Mun orbit, then go into map view and look at Kerbin - as you zoom out, the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E icon increases in size until it covers Kerbin.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInterestingly, as you zoom in (toward your ship), the icon shrinks to the point of being invisible while Kerbin grows in apparent size - so maybe this is just a case of an inverted scale factor?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Izzet","CreatedById":232019,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-01-04T21:59:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.2.0 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 11 Home 64-bit (10.0, Build 22621) | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0AMD Ryzen 5 5600G with Radeon Graphics | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0AMD Radeon RX 6700 XT | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E16384MB RAM\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSeverity : Low\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrequency : Only observed once\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe space centre icon does not scale when camera is rotated from an eccentric orbit and hence appears very large. I will add an image later, right now it is not possible to do so.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cstyle type=\u0022text/css\u0022\u003E\r\n.ipsImage {\r\nwidth: 900px !important;\r\n}\u003C/style\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Space Peacock","CreatedById":224498,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-01-04T22:01:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/232019-izzet/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022232019\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/232019-izzet/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Izzet\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0merged your report\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Anonymous Bug Reporter","CreatedById":231013,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-01-09T06:41:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.2.0 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0win 11 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0I9 14900kf | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A04090 | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E32gb @7200\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nin Map mode\u00A0 \u00A0when trying to plot an new flight path there is a ton of clutter and makes it a pain to adjust and move prograde/retro grade/ ect. The ships already orbiting a planet are extremely large and in 8bit graphics so large you cant click on the planet without focusing the ship first.\u00A0 That is a decent workaround but theres nothing i can do if i have a bunch of sats orbiting kerbin and im trying to plot a prograde burn out of kerbin theres soo much stuff the plotter node is lost in the clutter,\u00A0 \u00A0 When the part count gets over 70 the game grinds down with some janky builds\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cstyle type=\u0022text/css\u0022\u003E\r\n.ipsImage {\r\nwidth: 900px !important;\r\n}\u003C/style\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Speeding Mullet","CreatedById":62635,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-01-09T11:56:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong style=\u0022background-color:#f9f9f9;color:#2d3134;font-size:15px;\u0022\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#f9f9f9;color:#